Use a modern minimal SaaS dashboard style across the whole website.

Design direction:
- clean, soft, professional, premium, and highly readable
- similar to modern booking dashboards / admin panels
- not flashy, not overly decorative, not heavy gradients
- focus on clarity, spacing, and hierarchy
- use a neutral light background with white cards and subtle borders/shadows

Typography:
- use Inter as the main font everywhere
- fallback: sans-serif
- page titles should be bold and clear
- section headings should be semibold
- body text should be clean and readable
- small labels should use uppercase with slight letter spacing for a dashboard feel

Typography scale:
- page title: 28px, 700
- section title: 20px, 600
- card title: 16px, 600
- body text: 14px to 16px, 400 to 500
- small labels / meta text: 12px, uppercase, letter spacing

Color style:
- main page background: very light grey / off-white
- cards and panels: white
- primary text: dark navy / near-black
- secondary text: muted grey
- borders: very soft light grey
- use soft functional accent colors for statuses only

Status colors:
- pending: soft orange background with darker orange text
- confirmed: soft green background with darker green text
- standby / unassigned: soft yellow background with darker yellow-brown text
- conflicts / errors: soft red or pink background with darker red text
- info / neutral badges: light grey background with dark grey text

Cards / boxes:
- all main sections should be inside rounded white cards
- border radius should be soft and modern, around 14px to 18px
- use subtle borders and light shadows
- avoid harsh outlines
- cards should have generous padding and breathing room
- every major section should feel like a separate modular card

Buttons:
- rounded corners
- clear visual hierarchy
- primary buttons should use dark navy / near-black background with white text
- secondary buttons should be white or light grey with dark text and soft border
- warning / action buttons like assign should use soft yellow styling
- danger buttons like reject / cancel should use soft red styling
- buttons should feel modern and clean, not glossy

Spacing and layout:
- use a spacious grid layout
- keep consistent gaps between cards and sections
- card padding around 18px to 24px
- section gaps around 24px to 32px
- keep alignment neat and consistent
- use whitespace to make the UI feel premium

Tables and list items:
- use clean rows with soft separators
- keep rows compact but not cramped
- use badges/chips for statuses
- action buttons should align cleanly to the right
- text hierarchy should make guest name, time, and party size easy to scan quickly

Inputs and forms:
- modern rounded inputs
- light borders
- white background
- clear label above each field
- generous padding inside inputs
- compact and consistent sizing
- focus states should be subtle and polished

Overall visual language:
- soft rounded cards
- subtle elevation
- calm neutral background
- strong typography hierarchy
- minimal but polished
- professional booking/product dashboard feel
- consistent across public pages, customer pages, and admin pages

